---
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About - DemumuMind" description="What DemumuMind is building and why." currentPath="/about/">
  <div class="page-content">
    <PageHero
      eyebrow="Philosophy"
      title="Local-first tools with receipts, not mystique."
      lede="DemumuMind builds MCP servers, desktop apps, and AI infrastructure that stay inspectable, composable, and deterministic."
      meta={["Open source", "Windows-first", "Protocol-native"]}
    />

    <h2>Operating principles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Local-first:</strong> data stays on your machine and core paths keep working offline.</li>
      <li><strong>Composable:</strong> MCP-native from day one so tools can talk through a shared protocol instead of bespoke glue.</li>
      <li><strong>Deterministic:</strong> critical paths should produce the same output from the same inputs.</li>
      <li><strong>Evidence-backed:</strong> promotion, proof, and releases should leave receipts behind.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <ul class="stack-list">
      <li><span class="tag">Python</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">TypeScript</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">C#</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">.NET MAUI</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">WinUI 3</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">MCP</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">FastMCP</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">Ollama</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">HNSW</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">CUDA</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who</h2>
    <p>
      One developer shipping under the <a href="https://github.com/DemumuMind" rel="noopener">DemumuMind</a> organization.
      The point is not to look like a SaaS facade. The point is to ship useful, inspectable tools and make their quality legible.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
